com.lightbend.lagom.javadsl.api.deser

Class RawId

  • Object
    • com.lightbend.lagom.javadsl.api.deser.RawId

  • public final class RawId
extends Object
    A raw ID. A raw ID consists of an ordered list of path parameters, which are ordered as they appear in the path, and a map of query parameters. Raw ids are extracted fram the path according to a path spec. For example, the following path spec: 
         /blog/:blogId/post/:postId/comments?pageNo&pageSize
    With the following path: 
         /blog/123/post/456/comments?pageNo=2
    Will extract a raw ID with two path parameters, the first parameter being named blogId with a value of 123, the second value being named postId with a value of 456. It will also have two query string parameters, one named pageNo with a value of 2, the other named pageSize with an empty value. Raw ids are what IdSerializer uses to convert the extracted path information into an Id type, and back.
